Title: What is Excel?
Description: Training: With Excel on your PC, Mac, or mobile device, you can add, edit, and format data, create tables and charts, visualize data trends, and share your work with OneDrive.

Title: Create a workbook
Description: Training: You can create a workibook in Microsoft Excel, to organize your data and worksheets. Create a blank workbook or use a template. Watch this online ARTICLE to learn how.

Title: Insert or delete a worksheet
Description: Training: In this online training ARTICLE, learn how to add, rename, or delete worksheets in your Microsoft Excel workbook.

Title: Move or copy worksheets
Description: Training: In Microsoft Excel 2016 you can copy or move worksheets within your workbook or to another. See how in this online training course.

Title: Insert or delete rows or columns
Change the column width and row height
Freeze columns or rows
Description: Training: Watch this online training to see how to freeze columns or rows to keep them visible as you scroll through data in Microsoft Excel 2016.

Title: Hide or unhide columns
Description: Training: Learn how to hide or unhide columns you don't want to see by watching this ARTICLE training course for Microsoft Excel 2016.

Title: Select cell contents
Description: Training: In this online training ARTICLE, watch how to select cell contents in Microsoft Excel 2016.

Title: Format numbers in cells
Description: Training: In Microsoft Excel, you can display number formats as currency, percentages, decimals, dates, phone numbers, or social security numbers. Watch this ARTICLE to see how.

Title: Copy cell formatting
Description: Training: With copy and paste options, Format Painter, and dragging techniques, you can quickly copy cell formatting in Microsoft Excel 2016. Learn how in this online ARTICLE.
